<br>
This night she stops just inside the door, for sitting across the room is a man she had not seen there before.  She has seen him seldom lately, except for that one day hunting frost giants.  Yet even then they had not shared more than a few words.  She thought about leaving.  That last day, when she had resurrected him, was still strong in her mind.  She had learned things that day that she had always wanted to know, but also had never, really, wished to hear.  As she was turning to leave, she heard him call out, &quot;Can a man change his destiny? Can a life that is destined for pain and suffering for everyone around him be changed?&quot;<br>
<br>
Maritzia stops, half in, half out of the door.  She wants to leave, she truly does.  This man too often has made her question herself, her beliefs, all that she was.  But, she is a cleric of the Prime Healer...she cannot leave another in pain.  She turns back into the darken tavern and slowly approaches the man at the table.<br>
